2fa.directory.name: Microsoft To-Do
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA phone calls may not be available in all regions

2fa.directory.name: Skype
2fa.directory.notes: Must be associated with a Microsoft Account.

2fa.directory.name: OneDrive
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA phone calls may not be available in all regions

2fa.directory.name: Outlook.com
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA phone calls may not be available in all regions

2fa.directory.name: Xbox Live
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA phone calls may not be available in all regions

2fa.directory.name: GoDaddy
2fa.directory.notes: If hardware 2FA enabled, customer support by phone requires enabling back-up method.

2fa.directory.name: GitHub
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware tokens must have a backup method, either SMS or software token.

2fa.directory.name: Zoho Mail
2fa.directory.notes: YubiKey registration works only on the new version of Zoho Accounts. Only one (1) YubiKey may be registered at a time. Supported Devices: YubiKey NEO, YubiKey 4 Nano, YubiKey 4, YubiKey 4C, YubiKey 4C Nano, YubiKey NEO-n, YubiKey Edge, YubiKey Edge-n.

2fa.directory.name: 1Password
2fa.directory.notes: Teams using Duo with 1Password can't enable additional 2FA as it's already handled by Duo. Hardware tokens (not U2F) are only available through Duo.

2fa.directory.name: Twitter
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware 2FA requires enabling back-up method. SMS only available on select providers.

2fa.directory.name: Tutanota
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware 2FA not yet supported for their desktop & mobile apps.

2fa.directory.name: Facebook
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware 2FA requires also enabling a back-up method

2fa.directory.name: Yahoo Mail
2fa.directory.notes: Linked phone number required for 2FA.

2fa.directory.name: Colorado School of Mines
2fa.directory.notes: Only available for employees

2fa.directory.name: JetBrains
2fa.directory.notes: U2F only available for Hub account (e.g. YouTrack). Limited to one software token OR one hardware token.

2fa.directory.name: Dashlane
2fa.directory.notes: FIDO U2F is a Premium feature only.

2fa.directory.name: Dropbox
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware 2FA requires also enabling Software or SMS 2FA as a back-up.

2fa.directory.name: Bitbucket
2fa.directory.notes: An SSH key must be associated with your account to enable 2FA.

2fa.directory.name: bitwarden
2fa.directory.notes: Premium account required for Duo, YubiKey and FIDO U2F.

2fa.directory.name: LastPass
2fa.directory.notes: Availability of 2FA options depends on your account type.

2fa.directory.name: Perimeter 81
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA is only available for users on Premium and Enterprise plans.

2fa.directory.name: University of Washington
2fa.directory.notes: Available for employees only
